# Cloudflare Pages security headers for Prime guest portal.
# Applied at edge response time to all paths.
#
# DEPLOYMENT NOTE: HSTS header in this file requires Full (strict) SSL to be active
# on the hostel-positano.com zone before this file is deployed to production.
# Deploying HSTS over a non-strict SSL zone risks downgrade attacks on redirect loops.
# See: docs/plans/prime-edge-tls-hardening/plan.md — TASK-02/TASK-03 must complete first.
#
# CSP connect-src allow-list (do not remove without auditing Firebase calls):
#   - prime-f3652-default-rtdb  — Firebase Realtime Database (HTTP + WebSocket)
#   - identitytoolkit.googleapis.com — Firebase Auth (sign-in / token exchange)
#   - securetoken.googleapis.com    — Firebase Auth (token refresh)
#   - prime-f3652.firebaseapp.com   — Firebase authDomain (OAuth redirect host)

/*
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; connect-src 'self' https://prime-f3652-default-rtdb.europe-west1.firebasedatabase.app wss://prime-f3652-default-rtdb.europe-west1.firebasedatabase.app https://identitytoolkit.googleapis.com https://securetoken.googleapis.com https://prime-f3652.firebaseapp.com; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'
